<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1628,2016]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1701,1727]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the RTA of the 
<typeStatus box="[835,933,1701,1727]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">holotype</typeStatus>
which resembles an open mouth (of a monstrous fantasy creature) with several pointed teeth (Latin “rictus/rictum” means “widely open mouth”); noun in genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1628,2016]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1808,1835]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males distinguished from those of all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1850" box="[817,938,1809,1835]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Corythalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,938,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Corythalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: embolus base (EB) with prolateral extension in form of an elongated bulge; width of EB circle clearly more than half the width of tegulum, almost 2/3; embolus (E) distally pointed and with prolateral direction (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[213,266,1917,1944]" captionStart="FIGURE 64" captionStartId="124.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@124.[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 64. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: Paratypes from São Paulo (B M-9, IBSP 33503; C M-4, IBSP 53033) and Mato Grosso do Sul (D M-6, IBSP 53374), Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: E Holotype and F Paratype SMNK-ARA 02326 (in this specimen bulb expanded; thus basal and distal haematodocha recognisable) from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: G Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: H Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: I Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: J Holotype and K paratype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: L Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927517/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">64H</figureCitation>
). RTA in retrolateral view with distinct bend, distal part directed disto-ventrally and being clearly shorter and narrower than proximal part (
<figureCitation box="[539,647,1952,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 15B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[661,710,1953,1980]" captionStart="FIGURE 68" captionStartId="128.[151,250,1784,1809]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,491,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[197,1391,489,1765]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURE 68. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, retrolateral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: B Paratype M-1, IBSP 131451, from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: C Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: D Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: E Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: F Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: G Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: H Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad. Corythalia gasnieri sp. nov.: I Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia fimbriata: J Lectotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia argentinensis: K Holotype from Misiones, Argentina. Corythalia luctuosa: L Lectotype from St. Laurent du Maroni, French Guiana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927525" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927525/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">68E</figureCitation>
), RTA in ventral view subdistally with broad and deep incision exhibiting several teeth (
<figureCitation box="[427,535,1988,2015]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[546,599,1989,2016]" captionStart="FIGURE 64" captionStartId="124.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@124.[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 64. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: Paratypes from São Paulo (B M-9, IBSP 33503; C M-4, IBSP 53033) and Mato Grosso do Sul (D M-6, IBSP 53374), Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: E Holotype and F Paratype SMNK-ARA 02326 (in this specimen bulb expanded; thus basal and distal haematodocha recognisable) from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: G Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: H Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: I Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: J Holotype and K paratype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: L Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927517/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">64H</figureCitation>
).
