<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1164,2043]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,1164,1191]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description. Male:</emphasis>
total length 6.3, carapace length 3.0, maximal carapace width 2.0, width of eye rectangle 1.8, opisthosoma length 2.5, opisthosoma width 1.7, fovea length 0.23. EYES: AME 0.58, ALE 0.35, PME 0.09, PLE 0.30, AME–AME 0.04, AME–ALE 0.04, PME–PME 1.52, PME–PLE 0.26, ALE–PLE 0.68, PLE–PLE 1.24, clypeus height at AME 0.28, clypeus height at ALE 0.66. Cheliceral furrow with 1 promarginal and 1 retromarginal teeth. SPINATION: palp without spines. Legs: femur 
<date box="[759,835,1306,1334]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1500-01">I 1500</date>
, II–IV 1600; patella 
<date box="[1070,1146,1307,1334]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1000-01">I 1000</date>
, II–IV 1010; tibia I 3005, II 3004{3015}, III–IV 3133; metatarsus 
<date box="[614,692,1343,1369]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2014-01">I 2014</date>
, 
<date box="[705,795,1342,1369]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2024-02">II 2024</date>
{2025}, III 3134, IV 3144. MEASUREMENT OF PALP AND LEGS: palp 2.4 [0.8, 0.4, 0.2, 1.0], I 4.5 [1.4, 0.8, 1.0, 0.8, 0.5], II 4.6 [1.5, 0.8, 1.0, 0.8, 0.5], III 5.4 [1.8, 0.8, 1.1, 1.2, 0.5], IV 5.4 [1.7, 0.7, 1.2, 1.2, 0.6]. LEG FORMULA: 3&amp;421 (legs III &amp; IV with exactly the same length). COPULATORY ORGAN: embolus (E) quite short, pointed and distal section directed prolaterally; E about as long as 1/2 the width of tegulum (T) (
<figureCitation box="[524,632,1484,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[645,697,1484,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 64" captionStartId="124.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@124.[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 64. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: Paratypes from São Paulo (B M-9, IBSP 33503; C M-4, IBSP 53033) and Mato Grosso do Sul (D M-6, IBSP 53374), Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: E Holotype and F Paratype SMNK-ARA 02326 (in this specimen bulb expanded; thus basal and distal haematodocha recognisable) from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: G Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: H Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: I Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: J Holotype and K paratype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: L Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927517/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">64H</figureCitation>
). Embolus base (EB) broad (EB circle almost as broad as 2/3 the width of T), located centro-distally at T; T relatively short, but proximal tegulum lobe (PTL) distinct and with small prolateral lobe; T with double stacked S-shaped spermduct visible in retrolateral 1/2 to 2/3 (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1289,1555,1582]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1301,1353,1555,1582]" captionStart="FIGURE 64" captionStartId="124.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@124.[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 64. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: Paratypes from São Paulo (B M-9, IBSP 33503; C M-4, IBSP 53033) and Mato Grosso do Sul (D M-6, IBSP 53374), Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: E Holotype and F Paratype SMNK-ARA 02326 (in this specimen bulb expanded; thus basal and distal haematodocha recognisable) from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: G Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: H Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: I Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: J Holotype and K paratype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: L Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927517/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">64H</figureCitation>
). Cymbium relatively short and broad, distally conically converging and at distalmost section rounded to egg-tip-shaped. Palpal tibia short (length about 2/3 the width), with indistinct and flat ventral tibial bump (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1244,1625,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 15</figureCitation>
A–B, 64H, 68E). RTA quite broad, subdistally with broad and deep incision exhibiting several teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1200,1661,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1212,1264,1662,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 64" captionStartId="124.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@124.[190,1396,489,1776]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 64. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: Paratypes from São Paulo (B M-9, IBSP 33503; C M-4, IBSP 53033) and Mato Grosso do Sul (D M-6, IBSP 53374), Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: E Holotype and F Paratype SMNK-ARA 02326 (in this specimen bulb expanded; thus basal and distal haematodocha recognisable) from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: G Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: H Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: I Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: J Holotype and K paratype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: L Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927517/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">64H</figureCitation>
), in retrolateral view even broader and with distinct bend, distal part directed disto-ventrally and being clearly shorter and narrower than proximal part (
<figureCitation box="[380,488,1732,1759]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1065,1090]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,183,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[312,1276,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov., male holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. A–B left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927411/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 15B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[502,551,1733,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 68" captionStartId="128.[151,250,1784,1809]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,491,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[197,1391,489,1765]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURE 68. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, retrolateral view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: B Paratype M-1, IBSP 131451, from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: C Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: D Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: E Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: F Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: G Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: H Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad. Corythalia gasnieri sp. nov.: I Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia fimbriata: J Lectotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia argentinensis: K Holotype from Misiones, Argentina. Corythalia luctuosa: L Lectotype from St. Laurent du Maroni, French Guiana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927525" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927525/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">68E</figureCitation>
). COLOURATION: see genus description for conservative aspects. Carapace dark red-brown (
<figureCitation box="[337,437,1767,1794]" captionStart="FIGURE 57" captionStartId="117.[151,250,1605,1630]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,491,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@117.[160,1427,489,1580]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURE 57. Corythalia spp., photographic images of male specimens, dorsal view. Corythalia latipes: A Neotype from Bahia, Brazil. Corythalia conferta sp. nov.: B Paratype M-1, IBSP 131451, from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia drepane sp. nov.: C Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia antepagmenti sp. nov.: D Paratype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia ricti Bayer, sp. nov.: E Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia parva: F Lectotype from Brazil. Corythalia protensa sp. nov.: G Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia placata: H Male MCZ 20545-II (Paralectotype of Dynamius blandus) from Trinidad. Corythalia gasnieri sp. nov.: I Holotype from Amazonas, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927501/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 57E</figureCitation>
